# llm-wiki-bootstrap (Cline rules)

This project is an `llm-wiki-bootstrap` instance — a personal LLM-wiki knowledge base operated via five named workflows.

## Read this first

**`AGENTS.md`** at the project root is the canonical schema. Read it before any work. It defines the three-layer model, conventions, and the five workflows.

## Three-layer model

- `raw/` — immutable source material curated by the user. Read-only for you.
- `wiki/` — LLM-owned markdown. You are the sole writer.
- `AGENTS.md` — the schema. Co-evolved by user + you.

## Five workflows

Implemented as Claude Code slash commands at `.claude/commands/wiki-*.md`. In Cline, the user invokes them by natural language; you follow the prompt body of the corresponding `.claude/commands/wiki-<name>.md` file step-by-step.

| Workflow | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `wiki-init` | Scaffold an empty wiki structure (idempotent). |
| `wiki-extract <source>` | Acquire URL / file / image into `raw/`. |
| `wiki-ingest [<raw-file>]` | Run the 7-step pipeline. Hash via `scripts/body-hash.sh`. |
| `wiki-query <question>` | Answer from wiki; web-search + promote on gaps. `--visual [html\|pdf\|png]` also emits a diagram of the answer (archetype auto-picked). |
| `wiki-lint [--apply]` | Find issues; propose / apply fixes. |

Plus two **output workflows** that render/export an already-built wiki (read-only on `raw/` and `wiki/`):

| Workflow | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `wiki-visualize [graph\|mermaid\|slides\|serve] [target]` | Graph / slides / mermaid / local server. Wraps `scripts/visualize/*`. Mechanical: renders existing structure. |
| `wiki-flashcards [dir]` | Export `## Flashcards` sections to an Anki CSV. Wraps `scripts/wiki-to-anki.sh`. |
| `wiki-diagram "<intent>"` | Semantic: retrieve from wiki, score the 8 archetypes, user picks, generate a self-contained HTML poster to `diagrams/`. Contracts in `templates/infographic/`. |

## Hard rules

1. **Never write to `raw/`** except the three `ingested_*` frontmatter fields, only as the last step of `wiki-ingest`.
2. **`scripts/body-hash.sh`** is the canonical hash. Do not inline a different algorithm.
3. **Pure CommonMark.** No Obsidian / Cursor / IDE-specific extensions.
4. **Cite raw sources** inline with `(source: raw/<file>#<anchor>)`.
5. **Append log.md entries** for every ingest / promote / lint-apply.

## When in doubt

Read `AGENTS.md`, then `wiki/index.md`.
